<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Sam Frost is stripping off to raise awareness for breast cancer on The All New Monty: Guys and Gals.</p>

<p>But on Saturday the Home and Away star revealed to The Daily Telegraph that the experience was a 'rollercoaster' of emotions.  </p>

<p>The 31-year-old actress explained that doing the charity burlesque show brought up a lot of body insecurities. </p>

<p>Out of her comfort zone: Sam Frost (right) is stripping off on The All New Monty: Guys and Gals and she revealed to The Daily Telegraph that the experience was a 'rollercoaster' of emotions</p>

<p>'It is amazing how many things that you’ve forgotten about bubble to the surface when you’re doing something new and being outside your comfort zone,' she told the publication. </p>

<p>'It was a rollercoaster, to be honest,' she continued.</p>

<p>The former Bachelorette added that her lack of dancing skills didn't do anything to help. </p>

<p>Confidence: The 31-year-old actress explained that doing the charity burlesque show brought up a lot of her body insecurities</p>

<p>'I’m not a dancer , I was completely out of my comfort zone. A lot of anxieties about self-worth came up.'  </p>

<p>However, the blonde bombshell revealed on The Morning Show on Friday, that knowing she was stripping for a good cause helped her overcome many of her previous body insecurities.  </p>

<p>'I think as females, we all have our own insecurities and it is really daunting to have to strip on TV and then in front of a large crowd,' she said. </p>

<p>Support: Sam also credited her co-stars, including singer Danielle Spencer (right), with supporting her during rehearsals and in the lead-up to the live performance</p>

<p>'I think one of the biggest things that I was constantly reminded of was why were we doing it and it was breast cancer awareness.' </p>

<p>She added:  'Any time I would start stressing out or feel insecure or anxious, I would think of the greater picture.'</p>

<p>The All New Monty: Guys and Gals continues Sunday at 7pm on Channel Seven </p>

<p>Don't miss it: The All New Monty: Guys and Gals continues Sunday at 7pm on Channel Seven </p>
